## Refresh command

`scripts/sync-frontend.sh` reads its source dir from `ODYSSEUS_STATIC` (falls
back to this directory, frontend-vendor/, when unset):

  ODYSSEUS_STATIC=/path/to/upstream/odysseus/static scripts/sync-frontend.sh

Point it at a fresh upstream `static/` checkout to build+smoke-test against
the new version before committing it. To actually refresh the vendored copy
(not just build against it once), replace this directory's contents with the
new upstream tree (see docs/SHIPPING.md "Tier 1.5" for the original vendoring
process: revert workspace-specific renames back to "Odysseus"/`__AGENT_NAME__`
tokens, strip override-derived files that `frontend-overrides/` re-adds at
sync time), then re-run `scripts/sync-frontend.sh` (no ODYSSEUS_STATIC) and
verify it still builds clean — the DRIFT gate at the bottom of the script will
fail loudly (`FATAL: vendor drift`) if any anchor-guarded patch (Gary
easter-egg swaps, SerpAPI provider-map patch, welcome-subtitle patch, or the
SW precache/CACHE_NAME patch) no longer finds its expected text, which is
exactly the signal that this file's provenance note needs updating too.

After a refresh, update the "upstream revision" line above and the vendor-
touching history above (or just note the new range) in the same commit.
